| Config + Crash Recovery | **0.7** | Template incomplete, journal is write-only observability |
| Pub/Sub | **0.3** | No PEL recovery — crashes lose messages |
| Pipeline | **0.2** | Monolithic error handling kills feedback loop |
| Data Access | **0.0** | No timeout, no retry, no pool, N+1 connections |

### Top 3 Systemic Risks

1. **No PEL recovery system-wide** — After any crash, in-flight Redis Stream messages (trade outcomes, signals, commands) are permanently lost. The entire learning feedback loop depends on these.

2. **No QuestDB connection resilience** — Zero timeout, zero retry, zero pooling. A transient DB blip silently skips DMA/Kelly/EWMA updates, leaving model weights stale.

3. **AIM lifecycle has no guardrails** — String-literal states with no validation mean GUI commands can bypass feature gates, learning gates, and force any AIM active. Zero unit test coverage.

